CatDescriptText: Cutline of image published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, June 7, 1941, pg. 18, reads: "Central Baptist Fetes Its Youthful Pastor And Wife" - Words of praise and commendation flowed like water and were as plentiful as the delicious chicken a la king at the banquet Monday night in Central Baptist Church for the Rev. and Mrs. Cornell E. Talley. Upper left: John Cavanaugh, former Burgess of Homestead, Mrs. Talley, Rev. Talley, and Mrs. W.E. Tinker, seated at speaker's table...Staff photos by Harris"
TitMainTitle: John Cavanaugh, Martha Talley, Rev. Cornell E. Talley, and Mrs. W. E. Tinker, seated at banquet table, in Central Baptist Church for banquet honoring Rev. Talley
